en_162677_0	In collaboration with our sister stations,  Hiru TV  and Hiru FM, Gold FM cares together with RED CROSS has launched an initiative to set up health camps to provide medical care to victims of the disaster hit areas.
en_162677_1	The health camps were set up having identified that people are being challenged with the spread of disease.
en_162677_2	Accordingly Health Camps have been organized at the church of Our Lady of Assumption in Pahala Hungwella as well as the  Bodhirukkhaaraama Temple in Yabbaluwa South in Biyagama, Gampaha today.
en_162677_3	Similarly Gold FM along with our sister stations hiru TV and hiru FM as well as the Sri Lanka Red Cross Society will jointly conduct special  medical camps for those impacted by the inclement weather in Matara at St. Thomas’s Girls’ College, the Raahula College and Uyanwatta Junior College.
en_162677_4	Meanwhile, The 6th consignment of relief goods collected under Gold FM Cares initiative will be distributed among the disaster affected people in the Mathara district today.
en_162677_5	The 5th consignment of relief goods was distributed among the disaster affected people in the Galle district yesterday.
en_162677_6	Earlier, the 3rd and the 4th consignments were delivered to Kalutara and Ratnapura districts.
en_162677_7	The Gold FM cares initiative together with HIRU FM AND TV to support the disaster victims, is receiving a great response from People Island wide.
en_162677_8	The Gold Fm cares initiative launched covering many areas of the island is currently receiving a large number of aid at its collection points.
en_162677_9	Asia Broadcasting Corporation has decided to suspend distribution of cash prizes among its viewers and listeners and divert the funds to provide relief to the disaster affected people.
en_162677_10	In addition, it is significant that Asia Broadcasting Corporation has granted its own relief to that of the value of relief assistance provided by the people.
en_162677_11	Asia broadcasting corporation’s relief operation is determined to effectively distribute assistance to the victims who are severly affected by the disaster.
en_162677_12	We at Gold FM invite all of out listeners to be a part of GOLD FM Cares, for the benefit of our very own people affected by inclement weather.
